== Rice ==

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}. Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the
boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Curry ==

Meanwhile, trim the @Carrot{1}, then slice into 0.5cm thick rounds (no need to
peel). Peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}). Zest and cut the @Lime{1}(quartered) into wedges. Crush the
@Salted Peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}. Drain
the @Garlic & White Wine Scottish Mussels{1%pack} in a #colander{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large saucepan{} with a tight-fitting lid on high
heat. Once hot, add the carrot and @Sugar Snap Peas{80%grams}. Stir-fry until
tender, ~{2-3%mins}, then reduce the heat to medium.

Add the garlic, @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%grams}.
Fry for ~{1%min} more.

Stir in the @Coconut Milk{180%ml}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and @Sugar{1%tsp} for the
sauce and bring to the boil. Simmer for ~{1-2%mins}.

Drain the @Fish Pie Mix{1%pack} and pat dry with kitchen paper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Gently stir the fish pie mix and mussels through the curry sauce, then pop the
lid on. Simmer gently, stirring occasionally, until the fish is cooked and the
mussels are piping hot, ~{5-8%mins}. Discard any mussels that do not open.

> IMPORTANT: Mussels served in shell, beware of sharp edges or broken shell.
> Discard any that do not open. Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

When the fish and mussels are cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Add a
squeeze of lime juice and stir in the lime zest. Taste the curry and season
with salt, pepper, sugar and more lime juice if needed.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your bowls. Spoon over the
Thai style fish curry and sprinkle over the peanuts. Serve with any remaining
lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!